    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Can you be more specific on the problem you have? For me (1.0.0) everything works as expected. \nRaw cells content is put into the .tex files **as they are** (without any treatment), hence if you want to write something like `foo_bar` in the \"normal\" text you have to escape the underscore yourself `foo\\_bar`. (Exactly as you would do in LaTeX as underscores are only allowed in math environments without backslash). If you want the underscore in math mode, it should work without any additional means.\n"
  },
