    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "OK - checking with the notebook documentation, I see that that such cells are supposed to be passed on unmodified. Makes sense.\n\nThis wasn't a problem for me either - the fix was pretty quick. There is still a reasonable chance that a relatively naive  user will include underscores in a raw text field (I had been in the habit of using them when I didn't need markdown preprocessing). The inclusion of the underscore package in the preamble would prevent this from triggering an error, which I think would follow the dictum of \"least surprise.\"\n\nFor reference, in ubuntu, it's included in the texlive-latex-recommended package (as well as TeXLive and MikTeX). So, it's not guaranteed on super-lean systems, but is likely to be installed if you have installed LaTeX.\n"
  },
