    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "On super-lean systems you won't be able to compile the .tex documents anyway, as currently some slightly exotic packages are used to create the nice looking cells, so there shouldn't be any concerns.\n\nI'm actually against adding packages which might include such \"fuzzy features\" only, especially as it would not be enough to handle underscores alone. There are lots of issues you will met writing raw text without expecting this to be processed by latex (e.g. `$, \\` etc.).\n"
  },
