    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This might have been an impulse that other new coders wouldn't have. But basically, if I didn't need markdown processing, I tended to avoid using it. The notion of using \"unprocessed text\" seemed akin to using raw text.\n\nBut as you point out, simply using Markdown cells all the time seems like the right answer. For what it's worth, I always use the underscore package when I'm writing LaTeX as well, so that may again be a strange quirk on my part.\n"
